rComments: Honestly great dude, not too sure how he knew all of our names without interaction but gave a more intimate experience to the course. Very knowledgeable dude and I felt like he truly wanted to see us succeed and took all the students' feedback seriously. This course specifically will be significantly simpler if you have a chemistry background too.

professor Phillips is amazing. He explains the concepts you ll need for the tests. The assignment is not a walk in the park but it was the first time I actually learn something interesting while writing. That been said, his lect slide are heavy on chem so be prepared. But don't get scare he tests you on the basics. I absolutely loved it!

He's an amazing prof. Really cares about your learning and is always willing to talk to you and explain concepts in further detail if you need it. He tries his best to make lectures interesting. It was a small class so he learned everyone's names which was great. Material involved a lot of memorization but he always made sure you were well prepared

Prof, TA and the lectures were amazing. Prof was very reasonable and understanding. Enjoyed being part of his class as I learnt a lot and made new friends as prof puts you into random debate groups. Overall definitely take the course if you are even remotely interested, you will enjoy for sure!
